    Scope and Contents
WWII CONSCIENTIOUS OBJECTORS PROJECT 
Ann Benedict, wife of Donald Benedict, discusses the development of her personal ideology; teaching experiences; family background; views on feminism, civil rights, and social issues; sexist attitudes in society; women ministers; her involvement in the women's movement; ratification of the Equal Rights Amendment in Illinois through the Religious Coalition for the ERA (RCERA); and her involvement with the Religious Coalition for Abortion Rights. 1 tape, 90 min., 30 pp. 
Interview by C. Arthur Bradley 
